tion twice at 1am and 2am - who just lied and said it would finish in 15 minutes. By 2.45 I was in the lobby in my boxer shorts on the verge of a nervous breakdown screaming 'Shut the f*** up !'. Not a pretty sight.Due to get up at 7 for meetings, I overslept, but was determined to see the manager in the morning. He kept me waiting for ages, apparently 'in a meeting', then after hearing my complaint offered 150 dirhams compensation, then withdrew the offer as I had booked and paid through an agent. I have staying in many cheap and expensive hotels in my life, but I can catagorically say that this is the worst hotel that I have ever stayed in. The prestigious four star sign in the lobby just makes a mockery of the whole system. Beware..	
